    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p> Shivam wants to win an iPhone but he couldn't win one. Pratik (Mr. Poo Poo), who is quite rich and can buy entire apple company, is a good friend of Shivam. Mr. Poo Poo is ready to give Shivam an iPhone if he shows him some good programming skills but he is quite weak in programming. So he needs your help. Can you help Shivam in winning an iPhone ?\n<br>\n<br>\nThe problem given by Mr. Poo Poo is described below.\n<br> \n<br>\nInitially you are given an array of <b>N</b> numbers. You need to answer <b>M</b> queries over that array and array is 1-indexed.\n<br>\nThe queries are of two types:<br><br>\n<b>1 i b</b> - Change array element at ith index to <b>b</b>.<br> <br>\n<b>2 L R</b> - Find the <b>PooPoo sum</b> of all subsequences of array from <b>L</b> to <b>R</b>.Since answer can be large so print <b>PooPoo Sum modulo 1000000007</b>.\n<br><br> \n<b>PooPoo sum of a subsequence is the square of sum of all numbers in subsequence taken with alternated signs.</b>\n<br><br>\nFor example, A={1,2,3,4} and for query of 2nd type <b>L=2 </b> and <b>R=3</b> then answer is equal to PooPoo sum of {2,3} + PooPoo sum of {2} +PooPoo sum of {3}= (+2-3)^2 + (+2)^2 + (+3)^2 = 14.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line contains two integers <b>N</b>,<b>M</b> which is size of array and number of queries.Next <b>N</b> lines denote <b>ith</b> element of array. Next <b>M</b> lines contains any of the two types of query described above.\n<br>\nFor each query of 2nd type print the answer in a new line after taking mod with <b>1000000007</b>.\n<br>\n</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each query of 2nd type print the answer in a new line .</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b>,<b>M</b> \u2264 <b>10^5</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>A[i]</b> \u2264 <b>10^9</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>L</b> \u2264 <b>R</b>\u2264<b>N</b></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Subtasks</h3>\n<b>Subtask #1 (20 points), Time limit : 1 sec<br>\n1 \u2264 N \u2264 20 <br>\nM=1 (query of second type)<br><br>\nSubtask #2 (80 points), Time limit : 1 sec<br>\nOriginal Constraints </b>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b> \n\n4 3\n1\n2\n3\n4\n2 2 3\n1 2 5\n2 1 2\n<b>Output:</b>\n14\n42\n</pre>\n\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p> In the test case for first query possible subsequences are - {2},{3},{2,3} and <br> PooPoo sum =2^2+3^2+(2-3)^2=14 .<br> \nAfter second query new array would be (1,5,3,4).<br>\nNow, for third query possible subsequence are -{1},{5},{1,5} and<br> PooPoo sum=1^2+5^2+(1-5)^2=42.<br>\n</p>\n",
